KCl extractable aluminum approximates the exchangeable Al, and is a measure of the active acidity present in soils with a 1:1 water pH less than 5.5. It relates to the immediate lime requirement and the CEC of the soil.

Total Al is the aluminum measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored as percent of the element and reported as  percent oxide on the base of the size fraction used.

Bulk density, <2 mm fraction, 1/10 bar is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume being measured after equilibration at 1/10 bar water tension. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

Bulk density, <2 mm fraction, 1/3 bar is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume being measured after equilibration at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

Bulk density, oven dry (105 C) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured on oven dry (105 C) natural fabric (clods). It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

Bulk density, <2mm fraction, reconstituted, 1/3 bar is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured on reconstituted samples at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

Bulk density, <2mm fraction, reconstituted, oven dry is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured on oven dry (105 C) reconstituted samples. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

Bulk density, oven dry (105 C) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured on oven dry (105 C) natural fabric (clods). It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

original_name: Bulk Density, 1/3 Bar, Before Rewet (Organic Soils)
original_description: Bulk density, 1/3 bar rewet (organic soils) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume being measured after samples have been equilibrated at 1/3 bar water tension, air dried, and re-equilibrated at 1/3 bar tension.
Bulk density, 1/3 bar is estimated when no measured value exists. It has been estimated from rupture resistance, particle size distribution, and organic carbon.

Bulk density, 1/3 bar rewet (organic soils) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume being measured after samples have been equilibrated at 1/3 bar water tension, air dried, and re-equilibrated at 1/3 bar tension.

original_name: Bulk Density, Clod, Field Water Content
original_description: Bulk density, <2mm fraction, moist is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture on natural clods. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

original_name: Bulk Density, Compliant Cavity, Field Moisture
original_description: Bulk density (compliant cavity at field H20) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture content by the compliant cavity method. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

original_name: Bulk Density, Core, <2 mm fraction, Field Moist
original_description: Bulk density, <2mm fraction, field moist is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture. Measurements are made on known volume cores. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter, <2 mm base.

original_name: Bulk Density, Field Core, Field Moisture
original_description: Bulk density (field core at field H20) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture content by the field core method. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

Bulk density (syringe at field H20) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture content by the syringe method. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

original_name: Bulk Density, Whole Soil, Field Moist
original_description: Bulk density, whole soil, field moist, is the weight per unit volume of the whole soil, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture content by the balloon method. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter, on a whole soil base.

Bulk density, whole soil, moist is the weight per unit volume of the whole soil, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture in clods. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter, whole soil base.
